            ">Korean travel diplomacy</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/north-korea-tourism-un-sanctions-exemption.jpg" alt="Tourism remains one of the few sectors in North Korea not currently restricted by United Nations Security Council sanctions" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #a9a7af">
            <i>Tourism remains one of the few sectors in North Korea not currently restricted by United Nations Security Council sanctions. Credits: North's official Korean Central News Agency</i>
          </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> South Korea’s Unification Ministry is <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-spotlight-h1-1-reviewing-a-plan?source=website" target="_blank">reviewing a plan</a> to allow private citizens to visit places like Wonsan if North Korea opens these sites to foreign tourists. This would be the first attempt to restart tourism since 2008, when a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-spotlight-h1-2-group-tours-to-mount-kumgang?source=website" target="_blank">group tours to Mount Kumgang</a> were halted after a South Korean tourist was shot dead. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
        <strong>The why:</strong> This proposal is part of South Korean President’s efforts to loosen relations with North Korea. Meanwhile, North Korea is facing setbacks in attracting foreign visitors, despite efforts to appeal to Russian and Chinese tourists. Their newly <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-spotlight-h1-3-constructed-beach-resort?source=website" target="_blank">constructed beach resort</a>, which was seen as a tool to develop tourism, was closed to foreigners. South Korea believes that its tourism plans will help North Korea’s economy and encourage it towards dialogue.  
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
      <strong>The big picture:</strong> Analysts say North Korea cannot rely on Chinese and Russian tourists for the triumph of the Wonsan complex, as many prefer cheaper destinations in Southeast Asia. South Korea’s engagement with North Korea might also create friction with Washington.  
          </p>
      
        </mj-text>
