          <h2 style="font-size: 24px; line-height: 1.2; font-weight: 500">
          Israel’s targets humanitarian hub</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.5">
            <strong>Summary: Israel launches a ground offensive in Gaza, sparking international criticism over mass killings during aid delivery.</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
          <strong>The what:</strong> Israel began a combined <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-spotlight-h2-4-ground-and-air-assault?source=website" target="_blank">ground and air assault</a> on Deir al‑Balah in central Gaza, its first ground offensive since October 2023. Their military asserts Hamas has a combat-ready battalion and about 20 Israeli hostages there. At least three were killed and several were wounded, while Israel urged civilians to evacuate south to Al-Mawasi. 
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
        <Strong>The why:</strong> Deir al‑Balah, long seen as a refuge for displaced families, hosts Shuhada al‑Aqsa Hospital, UN offices, and other aid agencies. Analysts believe the latest offense is an attempt to force Hamas to a 60-day ceasefire and hostage agreement. Meanwhile, <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-spotlight-h2-5-humanitarian-groups-warn?source=website" target="_blank">humanitarian groups warn</a> the offensive will worsen conditions in already overcrowded shelters.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">
       <strong>The big picture:</strong> Between 50,000 and 80,000 people were ordered to evacuate. Following this, 28 countries have issued a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-spotlight-h2-6-joint-statement?source=website" target="_blank">joint statement</a> demanding an immediate end to the war. They criticized Israel’s aid delivery model and condemned the killing of 800 civilians. Israel’s foreign minister dismissed the criticism, saying it was disconnected from reality.   
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
