        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="
              font-size: 16px;
              line-height: 1.5;
              padding-top: 4px;
              padding-bottom: 6px;
            ">
          <strong>🇺🇦 Ukraine - More drone strikes</strong>. Russia's ongoing drone and missile attacks on Ukraine continue as Kyiv stepped up its attacks on Moscow, targeting airports and causing chaos. President Zelenskyy urges talks with Putin, but Russia remains unresponsive, despite US pressure for a ceasefire (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-worldwide-10-damage-report?source=website" target="_blank">damage report</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
         <strong>🇬🇷 Greece - Migrant surge in Crete</strong>. Greek authorities rescued 74 migrants in Crete, part of nearly 300 arrivals over the weekend, as smugglers shift routes from North Africa. Traffickers increasingly use longer Mediterranean crossings to bypass stricter patrols near Turkey. Greece plans to deploy navy ships near Libya to deter illegal migration (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-worldwide-11-cretean-arrivals?source=website" target="_blank">Cretean arrivals</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
        <strong>🇪🇨 Ecuador - Gang leader extradited</strong>. Ecuadorian gang leader Adolfo “Fito” Macías has been extradited to the US to face drug and arms trafficking charges. The leader of Los Choneros was recaptured in June after having escaped from prison. Linked to international cartels and a political assassination, Macías’s extradition follows Ecuador’s tough anti-crime stance amid rising violence and rampant cocaine smuggling through its ports (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-worldwide-12-drug-lord-captured?source=website" target="_blank">drug lord captured</a>).
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
        <strong>🌏Southeast Asia- Major drop in aid</strong>. Development aid to Southeast Asia is expected to drop by over $2B in 2026, as Western countries redirect funding to defense and domestic needs. Poorer nations, such as Myanmar and Laos, would face the greatest impact. As US and European aid declines, countries such as China, Japan, and South Korea are expected to assume a larger development role (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-worldwide-13-aid-shift?source=website" target="_blank">aid shift</a>).
          </p>
           <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5; padding-bottom: 6px">
      <strong>🇨🇿 Czechia - Anti communist law</strong>. Czech President Petr Pavel signed a law criminalizing the promotion of communist ideology, equating it with Nazi propaganda. Offenders face up to five years in prison. The amendment aims to address a perceived judicial imbalance. The Communist Party of Bohemia and Moravia condemned the move as political targeting, as it seeks re-entry into parliament in the upcoming elections (<a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-jul-25-worldwide-14-criminalizing-communism?source=website" target="_blank">criminalizing communism</a>).
          </p>
